            {
                "comment_id": 10,
                "post_id": 1,
                "user_id": 1,
                "content": "Yikes, this is stressing me out. I\u2019m a first-time buyer (28F, Emirati) saving for a mid-market apartment. If average mortgage rates are now above 6.5%, how does that translate to monthly payments? For example, if I borrow around AED 1M after a 20% down payment on a 25-year mortgage, what ballpark monthly payment would I be looking at? \n\nA few questions:\n- Are banks offering fixed-rate options or caps, or is everything variable tied to EIBOR now?\n- Will RERA/banks tighten affordability checks with this hike? I\u2019m worried about approval and ending up house-poor.\n- Is it smarter to wait 6\u201312 months and keep renting, or consider off-plan with developer payment plans (e.g., post-handover 60/40) to reduce interest exposure for now?\n- Do you expect mid-market areas (JVC, Town Square, Arjan, IMPZ) to cool with higher financing costs, or will prices stay sticky?\n- Are there any rate buydown offers, cashback, or fee waivers that can soften this? \n\nAny advice for a cautious first-time buyer would be really appreciated. I really want to buy, but the mortgage risk is making me anxious.",
                "created_at": "2026-04-27 08:36:56.743080",
