                "user_id": 3,
                "content": "Good, timely alert. As someone who\u2019s worked through two Dubai cycles, a 50 bps hike pushing mortgages above ~6.5% will mainly pressure the mid-market end-user. My read:\n\n- Buyers: re-run affordability with a +200 bps stress test; aim to keep total housing costs within a prudent share of income. Explore fixed vs EIBOR-linked options, larger down payments, and be realistic on service charges and future rate resets.\n- Sellers: expect longer days-on-market and pickier demand unless pricing matches recent comps. Quality, ready stock still moves; over-ambitious asks will sit.\n- Segments: cash-led prime less affected; off-plan with extended payment plans stays active, but secondary mid-tier likely cools first. Rentals may firm further as some would-be buyers step back.\n\nNot calling a bubble, but some froth in select mid-tier communities should deflate. Sensible pricing and disciplined underwriting will matter more over the next few quarters.",
