INFO - 2026-04-27 08:08:12,719 - social.agent - Agent 14 performed action: create_comment with args: {'post_id': 1, 'content': 'For anyone stressing about the math: AED 1M over 25 years at ~6.5% is roughly AED 6,700–6,900/month (plus insurance/fees). A +50 bps move is about +AED 300/month per AED 1M. Not fun, but not a collapse.\n\nOn the ground: I bought in Dubai Marina in 2019 and I’m selling now at ~+40% — viewings have been back-to-back. Prime, well-located stock is still moving; mid-market with high LTVs will be pickier.\n\nPractical tips:\n- If you’re here 5+ years, owning can still beat renting — rents keep climbing.\n- Ask banks for 2–3 year fixed/capped options and know the reversion rate.\n- Compare secondary vs off-plan with genuine post-handover plans (check RERA escrow/permits).\n- Negotiate the monthly: DLD fee waivers, small price trims, or service-charge credits.\n\nHeadlines ≠ reality. Run your numbers. If I weren’t moving back to the UK, I’d happily hold/buy again. #DubaiRealEstate #DubaiMarina'}
