INFO - 2026-04-27 08:09:23,900 - social.agent - Agent 5 performed action: create_comment with args: {'post_id': 7, 'content': 'Appreciate the cycle-aware packaging. At >6.5% mortgages, end-user math hinges on total cost of ownership and rate path. A few specifics would help buyers (and investors) price this correctly:\n\n- Partner-bank fixed: term, all-in APR, reversion rate/spread to EIBOR, lock validity.\n- Post-handover plans: effective IRR to developer (incl. fees), % of price payable post-handover, grace periods, penalties for prepayment.\n- Escrow and milestones: are collections tied to RERA-certified progress? Any calendar-based back-loading?\n- Buyer mix on these schemes (end-user vs investor) and default/late-payment experience on prior cohorts.\n- Typical service charges (AED/sqft) for the referenced inventory and projected OPEX trend.\n- Any rate buydown/cashback/DLD fee waivers—and the netback vs headline price.\n- Golden Visa thresholds and unit eligibility timelines.\n\nIn a tightening cycle, transparency on carry and cash flows beats slogans. Buyers should stress test at 8–9% and keep DBR within CBUAE caps; developers who publish full economics will clear faster.'}
